      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "Lee, that took some honesty to share, and I'm glad you did. What you're describing — the heavy legs, disrupted sleep, lost appetite, dreading runs, and an elevated resting HR — that's a cluster of signals your body is sending pretty clearly. You're not being soft. You're being smart by noticing it.\n\nHere's the thing about the \"I can't afford time off\" feeling: I understand it completely, especially with 10 weeks to go. But I want to offer a different frame, if that's okay.\n\n**What you're describing looks a lot like early overreaching** — the kind where continuing to push doesn't build fitness, it erodes it. An 8 bpm jump in resting HR alone is one of the most reliable signs your system is under stress. Training on top of that doesn't add to your fitness bank — it actually makes withdrawals.\n\nBefore I say more, I want to ask: **what do you think is driving the poor sleep and appetite loss?** Is it training load, life stress, or a combination? That matters a lot for figuring out the right path forward.\n\n---\n\nWhat I *can* tell you is this: **10 weeks is actually enough time** — but only if we protect the next 1-2 weeks so the following 7-8 can be productive. A runner who recovers now and trains well for 8 weeks will arrive at the start line in far better shape than one who grinds through 10 weeks depleted.\n\nI'd also gently suggest checking in with your GP or a sports medicine doctor, not because something is definitely wrong, but because persistent sleep disruption and appetite changes alongside training stress are worth a professional set of eyes. That's outside my lane, and you deserve proper support there.\n\nWithin my lane, I can absolutely adjust your plan to protect your goal while giving your body what it needs right now.\n\n**What feels more manageable to you — a short reduced-load week, or would you like to talk through what a recovery-forward 10-week block could look like?**"
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_01DRMhy6L8RXprf2NeUWmbaz"
    }
  ],
